<br>
In EQ, earlier this evening, I was surprised by a most generous individual.  On, weeknights it's difficult to find a group, so instead I turn to finding something to solo while I read a book during downtime.  Today the place was Oasis of Marr and the action was Spectre Island.  After a few rounds of battles, I get a tell from Nilditan, a 31 wizard from a guild I'm not familiar with, &lt;Reflections in the Dream&gt;.  He asks what level I am, I respond 47.  He then tells me, that he cannot take the mob he's attacking and suggests I kill it.<br>
I heed his advice and immediately zone to South Ro.  Upon entering the zone, I find something I've never encountered before, the Ancient Cyclops.  In short order the cyclops is dispatched and I am a new owner of a Ring of Ancients.<br>
<br>
Now, normally, I would be estatic and extremely hyperactive.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Don't get me wrong, I thanked this kind gentleman profusely, probably to the point of annoyance.  What has me taken aback, is the simple fact that he gave up his spawn to a complete stranger because he knew he could not handle it.  This kind of generosity reminds me of the reasons why I've played this game for years.  That the people behind these characters are capable of doing something kind and generous for another out of the goodness of their heart.<br>
I believe Nilditan could very easily have let the Ancient Cyclops despawn without notifying anyone at all, but he didn't.  And, that truly stands out and shows his character.  Maybe random acts of kindness really do work. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Although, Nilditan or any of his guildies, probably will never read this, I wanted to share this with those who do happen to see this.  Be kind and be generous, for you never know when things may smile upon you.<br>
<br>
-Wolfgann <p><BR>
